"1621","<PAGE>"
"1622","pursuant to the 1940 Act. In addition, where the effect of a requirement of the"
"1623","1940 Act reflected in any provision of this Agreement is revised by rule,"
"1624","regulation or order of the Commission, such provision shall be deemed to"
"1625","incorporate the effect of such rule, regulation or order. The duties and"
"1626","obligations of the parties under this Agreement shall be governed by and"
"1627","construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Delaware to the extent"
"1628","that state law is not preempted by the provisions of any law of the United"
"1629","States heretofore or hereafter enacted."
"1630","     SECTION 20. AMENDMENT OF THIS AGREEMENT. This Agreement supersedes the"
"1631","advisory agreement between the parties hereto dated March 1, 2001. No provision"
"1632","of this Agreement may be changed, waived, discharged or terminated orally, but"
"1633","only by an instrument in writing signed by the party against which enforcement"
"1634","of the change, waiver, discharge or termination is sought. If shareholder"
"1635","approval of an amendment is required under the 1940 Act, no such amendment shall"
"1636","become effective until approved by a vote of the majority of the outstanding"
"1637","shares of the affected Funds. Otherwise, a written amendment of this Agreement"
"1638","is effective upon the approval of the Board and the Adviser."
"1639","     SECTION 21. WELLS FARGO NAME. The Adviser and the Trust each agree that the"
"1640","name Wells Fargo, which comprises a component of the Trust's name, is a"
"1641","property right of the parent of the Adviser. The Trust agrees and consents that:"
"1642","(i) it will use the words Wells Fargo as a component of its corporate name,"
"1643","the name of any series or class, or all of the above, and for no other purpose;"
"1644","(ii) it will not grant to any third party the right to use the name Wells
Fargo for any purpose; (iii) the Adviser or any corporate affiliate of the"
"1645","Adviser may use or grant to others the right to use the words Wells Fargo, or"
"1646","any combination or abbreviation thereof, as all or a portion of a corporate or"
"1647","business name or for any commercial purpose, other than a grant of such right to"
"1648","another registered investment company not advised by the Adviser or one of its"
"1649","affiliates; and (iv) in the event that the Adviser or an affiliate thereof is no"
"1650","longer acting as investment adviser to any Fund, the Trust shall, upon request"
"1651","by the Adviser, promptly take such action as may be necessary to change its"
"1652","corporate name to one not containing the words Wells Fargo and following such"
"1653","change, shall not use the words Wells Fargo, or any combination thereof, as a"
"1654","part of its corporate name or for any other commercial purpose, and shall use"
"1655","its best efforts to cause its trustees, officers and shareholders to take any"
"1656","and all actions that the Adviser may request to effect the foregoing and to"
"1657","reconvey to the Adviser any and all rights to such words."
"1658","     SECTION 22. RISK ACKNOWLEDGEMENT. The Adviser does not guarantee the future"
"1659","performance of the Funds or any specific level of performance, the success of"
"1660","any investment decision or strategy that the Adviser may use, or the success of"
"1661","the Adviser's overall management of the Funds. The Trust understands that"
"1662","investment decisions made for the Funds by the Adviser are subject to various"
"1663","market, currency, economic and business risks, and that those investment"
"1664","decisions will not always be profitable. The Adviser will manage only the"
"1665","securities, cash and other investments for which management responsibility is"
"1666","delegated to it and which are held in the Funds' account(s) and, in making"
"1667","investment decisions for the Funds, the Adviser will not consider any other"
"1668","securities, cash or other investments owned by the Trust."
