"2294","<DESCRIPTION>AUDIT LETTER"
"2295","<TEXT>"
"2296","Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm"
"2297","To the Board of Trustees and Shareholders of"
"2298","Wells Fargo Funds Trust:"
"2299","In planning and performing our audits of the financial"
"2300","statements of the Wells Fargo Advantage Asia Pacific Fund,"
"2301","Wells Fargo Advantage Diversified International Fund,"
"2302","Wells Fargo Advantage Emerging Markets Equity Fund, Wells"
"2303","Fargo Advantage Emerging Markets Equity Income Fund, Wells"
"2304","Fargo Advantage Emerging Markets Local Bond Fund, Wells"
"2305","Fargo Advantage Global Opportunities Fund, Wells Fargo"
"2306","Advantage International Bond Fund, Wells Fargo Advantage"
"2307","International Equity Fund, Wells Fargo Advantage Intrinsic"
"2308","Small Cap Value Fund, Wells Fargo Advantage Intrinsic World"
"2309","Equity Fund, Wells Fargo Advantage Small Cap Opportunities"
"2310","Fund, Wells Fargo Advantage Small Cap Value Fund, Wells"
"2311","Fargo Advantage Small/Mid Cap Value Fund, Wells Fargo"
"2312","Advantage Special Small Cap Value Fund, Wells Fargo"
"2313","Advantage Stategic Income Fund, and Wells Fargo Advantage"
"2314","Traditional Small Cap Growth Fund (the Funds), sixteen of"
"2315","the funds comprising the Wells Fargo Funds Trust, as of and"
"2316","for the year ended October 31, 2013, in accordance with the"
"2317","standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board"
"2318","(United States), we considered the Funds' internal control"
"2319","over financial reporting, including controls over"
"2320","safeguarding securities, as a basis for designing our"
"2321","auditing procedures for the purpose of expressing our"
"2322","opinion on the financial statements and to comply with the"
"2323","requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for the purpose of"
"2324","expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the Funds'"
"2325","internal control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we"
"2326","express no such opinion."
"2327","Management of the Funds are responsible for establishing"
"2328","and maintaining effective internal control over financial"
"2329","reporting. In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and"
"2330","judgments by management are required to assess the expected"
"2331","benefits and related costs of controls. A fund's internal"
"2332","control over financial reporting is a process designed to"
"2333","provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of"
"2334","financial reporting and the preparation of financial"
"2335","statements for external purposes in accordance with"
"2336","generally accepted accounting principles. A fund's internal"
"2337","control over financial reporting includes those policies and"
"2338","procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of records"
"2339","that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect"
"2340","the transactions and dispositions of the assets of the fund;"
"2341","(2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are"
"2342","recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial"
"2343","statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting"
"2344","principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the fund"
"2345","are being made only in accordance with authorizations of"
"2346","management and directors of the fund; and (3) provide"
"2347","reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely"
"2348","detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition"
"2349","of the fund's assets that could have a material effect on"
"2350","the financial statements."
"2351","Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over"
"2352","financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements."
"2353","Also, projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to"
"2354","future periods are subject to the risk that controls may"
"2355","become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that"
"2356","the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures"
"2357","may deteriorate."
"2358","A deficiency in internal control over financial reporting"
"2359","exists when the design or operation of a control does not"
"2360","allow management or employees, in the normal course of"
"2361","performing their assigned functions, to prevent or detect"
"2362","misstatements on a timely basis. A material weakness is a"
"2363","deficiency, or a combination of deficiencies, in internal"
"2364","control over financial reporting, such that there is a"
"2365","reasonable possibility that a material misstatement of the"
"2366","Funds' annual or interim financial statements will not be"
"2367","prevented or detected on a timely basis."
"2368","Our consideration of the Funds' internal control over"
"2369","financial reporting was for the limited purpose described"
"2370","in the first paragraph and would not necessarily disclose"
"2371","all deficiencies in internal control that might be material"
"2372","weaknesses under standards established by the Public Company"
"2373","Accounting Oversight Board (United States). However, we"
"2374","noted no deficiencies in the Funds' internal control over"
"2375","financial reporting and their operation, including controls"
"2376","over safeguarding securities that we consider to be a"
"2377","material weakness as defined above as of October 31, 2013."
"2378","This report is intended solely for the information and use"
"2379","of management and the Board of Trustees of Wells Fargo Funds"
"2380","Trust and the Securities and Exchange Commission and is not"
"2381","intended to be and should not be used by anyone other than"
"2382","these specified parties."
"2383","/s/ KPMG LLP"
"2384","Boston, Massachusetts"
"2385","December 23, 2013"
"2386","</TEXT>"
