"3987","     SECTION 10. STANDARD OF CARE. The Trust and the Adviser will expect of the"
"3988","Sub-Adviser, and the Sub-Adviser will give the Trust and the Adviser the benefit"
"3989","of, the Sub-Adviser's best judgment and efforts in rendering its services to the"
"3990","Trust, and the Sub-Adviser shall not be liable hereunder for any mistake in"
"3991","judgment. In the absence of willful misfeasance, bad faith, gross negligence or"
"3992","reckless disregard of obligations or duties hereunder on the part of the"
"3993","Sub-Adviser or any of its officers, directors, employees or agents, the"
"3994","Sub-Adviser shall not be subject to liability to the Adviser, to the Trust or to"
"3995","any shareholders in the Trust for any act or omission in the course of, or"
"3996","connected with, rendering services hereunder or for any losses that may be"
"3997","sustained in the purchase, holding or sale of any security. Notwithstanding the"
"3998","foregoing, the Sub-Adviser shall be responsible for the accuracy and"
"3999","completeness (and liability for the lack thereof) of the statements and any Data"
"4000","(only if Sub-Adviser furnishes to Adviser or the Trust any such Data for"
"4001","inclusion in Fund documents) furnished by the Sub-Adviser for use by the Adviser"
"4002","in the Fund's offering materials (including the prospectus, the statement of"
"4003","additional information, advertising and sales materials) and any proxy"
"4004","statements that pertain to the Sub-Adviser, the portfolio managers of the Fund"
"4005","and the investment of the Fund's assets."
"4006","     Nothing in this Agreement (including Sections 10, 15 or 16 of this"
"4007","Agreement) shall be construed to relieve either the Sub-Adviser or the Adviser"
"4008","of any claims or liability arising under federal securities laws or any"
"4009","non-waivable provisions of any other federal or state laws."
