"4323","     This AMENDED AND RESTATED AGREEMENT is made as of this 1st day of June,"
"4324","2010, as amended and restated as of November 7, 2012, by and among Wells"
"4325","Fargo Funds Trust (the Trust), a statutory trust organized under the laws of"
"4326","the State of Delaware with its principal place of business at 525 Market Street,"
"4327","12th Floor, San Francisco, California 94105, Wells Fargo Funds Management, LLC"
"4328","(the Adviser), a limited liability company organized under the laws of the"
"4329","State of Delaware with its principal place of business at 525 Market Street,"
"4330","12th Floor, San Francisco, California 94105, and Metropolitan West Capital"
"4331","Management, LLC (the Sub-Adviser), a limited liability company organized under"
"4332","the laws of the State of California, with its principal place of business at 610"
"4333","Newport Center Drive, Suite 1000, Newport Beach, CA 92660."
"4334","     WHEREAS, the Adviser and the Sub-Adviser are registered investment advisers"
"4335","under the Investment Advisers Act of 1940, as amended (the Advisers Act); and"
"4336","     WHEREAS, the Trust is engaged in business as an open-end investment company"
"4337","with one or more series of shares and is registered under the Investment Company"
"4338","Act of 1940, as amended (the 1940 Act); and"
"4339","     WHEREAS, the Trust's Board of Trustees (the Board) has engaged the"
"4340","Adviser to perform investment advisory services for each series of the Trust"
"4341","under the terms of an investment advisory agreement, dated August 6, 2003,"
"4342","between the Adviser and the Trust (the Advisory Agreement); and"
"4343","     WHEREAS, the Adviser, acting pursuant to the Advisory Agreement, wishes to"
"4344","retain the Sub-Adviser, and the Trust's Board has approved the retention of the"
"4345","Sub-Adviser, to provide investment advisory services to each series of the Trust"
"4346","listed in Appendix A hereto as it may be amended from time to time (each a"
"4347","Fund and collectively the Funds), and the Sub-Adviser is willing to provide"
"4348","those services on the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement;"
"4349","     NOW THEREFORE, the Trust, the Adviser and Sub-Adviser agree as follows:"
"4350","     SECTION 1. APPOINTMENT OF SUB-ADVISER. The Trust is engaged in the business"
"4351","of investing and reinvesting its assets in securities of the type and in"
"4352","accordance with the limitations specified in its Declaration of Trust, as"
"4353","amended or supplemented from time to time, By-Laws (if any) and Registration"
"4354","Statement filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the Commission)"
"4355","under the 1940 Act and the Securities Act of 1933 (the Securities Act),"
"4356","including any representations made in the prospectus and statement of additional"
"4357","information relating to the Funds contained therein and as may be amended or"
"4358","supplemented from time to time, all in such manner and to such extent as may"
"4359","from time to time be authorized by the Board."
"4360","                                      -1-"
"4361","<PAGE>"
"4362","     Subject to the direction and control of the Board, the Adviser manages the"
"4363","investment and reinvestment of the assets of the Funds and provides for certain"
"4364","management and other services as specified in the Advisory Agreement."
"4365","     Subject to the direction and control of the Board and the Adviser, the"
"4366","Sub-Adviser shall manage the investment and reinvestment of the assets of the"
"4367","Funds as specified in this Agreement, and shall provide the management and other"
"4368","services specified below in Section 2(a), all in such manner and to such extent"
"4369","as may be directed in writing from time to time by the Adviser. Notwithstanding"
"4370","anything in this Agreement to the contrary, the Adviser shall be responsible for"
"4371","compliance with any statute, rule, regulation, guideline or investment"
"4372","restriction that applies to the Funds' investment portfolio as a whole and the"
"4373","Sub-Adviser's responsibility and liability shall be limited to following any"
"4374","written instruction the Sub-Adviser receives from the Adviser."
"4375","     The investment authority granted to the Sub-Adviser shall include the"
"4376","authority to exercise whatever powers the Trust may possess with respect to any"
"4377","of its assets held by the Funds, including, but not limited to, the power to"
"4378","exercise rights, options, warrants, conversion privileges, redemption"
"4379","privileges, and to tender securities pursuant to a tender offer. The Sub-Adviser"
"4380","shall not, however, be responsible for voting proxies, for participating in"
"4381","class actions and/or other legal proceedings on behalf of the Funds, but will"
"4382","provide such assistance as is reasonably requested in writing by the Adviser."
"4383","     SECTION 2. DUTIES, REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES OF THE SUB-ADVISER."
"4384","     (a) The Sub-Adviser shall make decisions with respect to all purchases and"
"4385","sales of securities and other investment assets for the Funds. To carry out such"
"4386","decisions, the Sub-Adviser is hereby authorized, as agent and attorney-in-fact"
"4387","for the Trust, for the account of, at the risk of and in the name of the Trust,"
"4388","to place orders and issue instructions with respect to those transactions of the"
"4389","Funds. In all purchases, sales and other transactions in securities and other"
"4390","assets for the Funds, the Sub-Adviser is authorized to exercise full discretion"
"4391","and act for the Trust and instruct the Fund's custodian (the Custodian) in the"
"4392","same manner and with the same force and effect as the Trust might or could do"
"4393","with respect to such purchases, sales or other transactions, as well as with"
"4394","respect to all other things necessary or incidental to the furtherance or"
"4395","conduct of such purchases, sales or other transactions."
"4396","     The Sub-Adviser acknowledges that the Funds and other mutual funds advised"
"4397","by the Adviser (collectively, the fund complex) may engage in transactions"
"4398","with certain sub-advisers in the fund complex (and their affiliated persons)"
"4399","in reliance on exemptions under Rule 10f-3, Rule 12d3-1, Rule 17a-10 and Rule"
"4400","17e-1 under the 1940 Act.  Accordingly, the Sub-Adviser hereby agrees that it"
"4401","will not consult with any other sub-adviser of a fund in the fund complex that"
"4402","is not an affiliated person (as that term is defined in the 1940 Act) of Wells"
"4403","Fargo & Company (Wells Fargo), or an affiliated person of such a sub-adviser,"
"4404","concerning transactions for a fund in securities or other fund assets.  With"
"4405","respect to a multi-managed Fund, the Sub-Adviser shall be limited to managing"
"4406","only the discrete portion of the Fund's portfolio as may be determined from"
"4407","time-to-time by the Board or the Adviser, and shall not consult with any sub-"
"4408","adviser that is not an affiliated person of Wells Fargo as to any other portion"
"4409","of the Fund's portfolio concerning transactions for the Fund in securities or"
"4410","other Fund assets."
"4411","                                      -2-"
"4412","<PAGE>"
"4413","     (b) Following the close of each calendar quarter, the Sub-Adviser will"
"4414","report to the Board regarding the investment performance of the Funds since the"
"4415","prior report, and will also keep the Board informed of important developments"
"4416","known by it to affect the Trust, the Fund and the Sub-Adviser, and on its own"
"4417","initiative will furnish the Board and the Adviser from time to time with such"
"4418","information as the Sub-Adviser, in its sole discretion, believes appropriate,"
"4419","whether concerning the individual companies whose securities are held by a Fund,"
"4420","the industries in which they engage, or the economic, social or political"
"4421","conditions prevailing in each country in which the Fund maintains investments."
"4422","The Sub-Adviser will also furnish the Board and the Adviser with such"
"4423","statistical and analytical information with respect to securities held by the"
"4424","Funds as the Sub-Adviser, in its sole discretion, believes appropriate or as the"
"4425","Board or the Adviser may reasonably request in writing."
"4426","     The Sub-Adviser shall promptly notify the Adviser of (i) any material"
"4427","changes regarding the Sub-Adviser that would impact disclosure in the Trust's"
"4428","Registration Statement, or (ii) any material violation of any requirement,"
"4429","provision, policy or restriction that the Sub-Adviser is required to comply with"
"4430","under Section 6 of this Agreement. The Sub-Adviser shall, within two business"
"4431","days, notify both the Adviser and the Trust of any legal process served upon it"
"4432","in connection with its activities hereunder, including any legal process served"
"4433","upon it on behalf of the Adviser, the Funds or the Trust. The Sub-Adviser, upon"
"4434","the written request of the Custodian, shall reasonably cooperate with the"
"4435","Custodian in the Custodian's processing of class actions or other legal"
"4436","proceedings relating to the holdings (historical and/or current) of the Funds."
"4437","     (c) The Sub-Adviser may from time to time employ or sub-contract the"
"4438","services of certain persons as the Sub-Adviser believes to be appropriate or"
"4439","necessary to assist in the execution of the Sub-Adviser's duties hereunder;"
"4440","provided, however, that the employment of or sub-contracting to any such person"
"4441","shall not relieve the Sub-Adviser of its responsibilities or liabilities"
"4442","hereunder. The cost of performance of such duties shall be borne and paid by the"
"4443","Sub-Adviser. No obligation may be imposed on the Trust in any such respect."
"4444","     The Sub-Adviser shall supervise and monitor the activities of its"
"4445","representatives, personnel and agents in connection with the execution of its"
"4446","duties and obligations hereunder. The appropriate personnel of the Sub-Adviser"
"4447","will be made available to consult with the Adviser, the Trust and the Board at"
"4448","reasonable times and upon reasonable notice concerning the business of the"
"4449","Trust."
"4450","     (d) The Sub-Adviser shall maintain records relating to portfolio"
"4451","transactions and the placing and allocation of brokerage orders as are required"
"4452","to be maintained by the Trust under the 1940 Act. The Sub-Adviser shall prepare"
"4453","and maintain, or cause to be prepared and maintained, in such form, for such"
"4454","periods and in such locations as may be required by applicable federal"
"4455","securities laws, the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, and Employee"
"4456","Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, as amended, including the rules and"
"4457","regulations thereunder, all documents and records relating to the services"
"4458","provided by the Sub-Adviser pursuant to this Agreement required to be prepared"
"4459","and maintained by the Trust. The books and records pertaining to the Trust which"
"4460","are in possession of the Sub-Adviser shall be the property of the Trust. The"
"4461","Trust, or the Trust's authorized representatives (including the"
"4462","                                      -3-"
"4463","<PAGE>"
"4464","Adviser), shall have access to such books and records at all times during the"
"4465","Sub-Adviser's normal business hours. Upon the reasonable written request of the"
"4466","Trust, copies of any such books and records shall be provided promptly by the"
"4467","Sub-Adviser to the Trust or the Trust's authorized representatives."
"4468","     (e) The Sub-Adviser represents and warrants to the Adviser and the Trust"
"4469","that: (i) the retention of the Sub-Adviser as contemplated by this Agreement is"
"4470","authorized by the Sub-Adviser's governing documents; (ii) the execution,"
"4471","delivery and performance of this Agreement does not violate any obligation by"
"4472","which the Sub-Adviser or its property is bound, whether arising by contract,"
"4473","operation of law or otherwise; (iii) this Agreement has been duly authorized by"
"4474","appropriate action of the Sub-Adviser and when executed and delivered by the"
"4475","Sub-Adviser will be the legal, valid and binding obligation of the Sub-Adviser,"
"4476","enforceable against the Sub-Adviser in accordance with the terms hereof,"
"4477","subject, as to enforcement, to applicable bankruptcy, insolvency and similar"
"4478","laws affecting creditors' rights generally and to general equitable principles"
