"4580","proxy."
"4581","     SECTION 8. EXPENSES. All of the ordinary business expenses incurred in the"
"4582","operations of the Funds and the offering of its shares shall be borne by the"
"4583","Funds unless specifically provided otherwise in this Agreement. The expenses"
"4584","borne by the Funds include, but are not limited to, brokerage commissions,"
"4585","taxes, legal, auditing or governmental fees, the cost of preparing share"
"4586","certificates, custodian, transfer agent and shareholder service agent costs,"
"4587","expense of issue, sale, redemption and repurchase of shares, expenses of"
"4588","registering and qualifying shares for sale, expenses relating to Board and"
"4589","shareholder meetings, the cost of preparing and distributing reports and notices"
"4590","to shareholders, the fees and other expenses incurred by the Funds in connection"
"4591","with membership in investment company organizations and the cost of printing"
"4592","copies of prospectuses and statements of additional information distributed to"
"4593","the Funds' shareholders."
"4594","     The Sub-Adviser shall pay its own expenses in connection with the services"
"4595","to be provided by it pursuant to this Agreement. In addition, the Sub-Adviser"
"4596","shall be responsible for reasonable out-of-pocket costs and expenses incurred by"
"4597","the Adviser or the Trust: (a) to amend the Trust's registration statement (other"
"4598","than as part of a normal annual updating of the registration statement) or"
"4599","supplement the Fund's prospectus, and circulate the same, solely to reflect a"
"4600","change in the personnel of the Sub-Adviser responsible for making investment"
"4601","decisions in relation to the Fund; or (b) to obtain shareholder approval of a"
"4602","new sub-advisory agreement as a result of a change in control (as such term is"
"4603","defined in Section 2(a)(9) of the 1940 Act) of"
"4604","                                      -6-"
"4605","<PAGE>"
"4606","the Sub-Adviser, or to otherwise comply with the 1940 Act, the Securities Act,"
"4607","or any other applicable statute, law, rule or regulation, as a result of such"
"4608","change."
"4609","     SECTION 9. COMPENSATION. As compensation for the sub-advisory services"
"4610","provided under this Agreement, the Adviser shall pay the Sub-Adviser fees,"
"4611","payable monthly, at the annual rates indicated on Appendix B hereto, as such"
"4612","Appendix may be amended or supplemented as agreed to in writing by the parties"
"4613","from time to time. It is understood that the Adviser shall be responsible for"
"4614","the Sub-Adviser's fee for its services hereunder, and the Sub-Adviser agrees"
"4615","that it shall have no claim against the Trust or the Funds with respect to"
"4616","compensation under this Agreement."
"4617","     SECTION 10. STANDARD OF CARE. The Trust and the Adviser will expect of the"
"4618","Sub-Adviser, and the Sub-Adviser will give the Trust and the Adviser the benefit"
"4619","of, the Sub-Adviser's best judgment and efforts in rendering its services to the"
"4620","Trust, and the Sub-Adviser shall not be liable hereunder for any mistake in"
"4621","judgment. In the absence of willful misfeasance, bad faith, gross negligence or"
"4622","reckless disregard of obligations or duties hereunder on the part of the"
"4623","Sub-Adviser or any of its officers, directors, employees or agents, the"
"4624","Sub-Adviser shall not be subject to liability to the Adviser, to the Trust or to"
"4625","any shareholders in the Trust for any act or omission in the course of, or"
"4626","connected with, rendering services hereunder or for any losses that may be"
"4627","sustained in the purchase, holding or sale of any security. Notwithstanding the"
"4628","foregoing, the Sub-Adviser shall be responsible for the accuracy and"
"4629","completeness (and liability for the lack thereof) of the statements and any Data"
"4630","(only if Sub-Adviser furnishes to Adviser or the Trust any such Data for"
"4631","inclusion in Fund documents) furnished by the Sub-Adviser for use by the Adviser"
"4632","in the Fund's offering materials (including the prospectus, the statement of"
"4633","additional information, advertising and sales materials) and any proxy"
"4634","statements that pertain to the Sub-Adviser, the portfolio managers of the Fund"
"4635","and the investment of the Fund's assets."
"4636","     Nothing in this Agreement (including Sections 10, 15 or 16 of this"
"4637","Agreement) shall be construed to relieve either the Sub-Adviser or the Adviser"
"4638","of any claims or liability arising under federal securities laws or any"
"4639","non-waivable provisions of any other federal or state laws."
"4640","     SECTION 11. NON-EXCLUSIVITY. The services of the Sub-Adviser to the Adviser"
"4641","and the Trust are not to be deemed to be exclusive, and the Sub-Adviser shall be"
"4642","free to render investment advisory and administrative or other services to"
"4643","others (including other investment companies) and to engage in other activities."
"4644","It is understood and agreed that officers or directors of the Sub-Adviser are"
"4645","not prohibited from engaging in any other business activity or from rendering"
"4646","services to any other person, or from serving as partners, officers, directors"
"4647","or trustees of any other firm or trust, including other investment advisory"
"4648","companies."
"4649","     It is understood that the Sub-Adviser performs investment advisory services"
"4650","for various clients, including accounts of clients in which the Sub-Adviser or"
"4651","associated persons have a beneficial interest. The Sub-Adviser may give advice"
"4652","and take action in the performance of its duties with respect to any of its"
"4653","other clients, which may differ from the advice given, or the timing or nature"
"4654","of action taken, with respect to the assets of the Funds. Nothing in this"
"4655","Agreement shall be deemed to impose upon the Sub-Adviser any obligation to"
"4656","purchase or sell"
"4657","                                      -7-"
"4658","<PAGE>"
"4659","for the Funds any security or other property that the Sub-Adviser purchases or"
"4660","sells for its own accounts or for the account of any other client."
"4661","     Any information or recommendations supplied by the Sub-Adviser to the"
"4662","Adviser or the Trust in connection with the performance of its obligations"
"4663","hereunder shall be treated as confidential and for use by the Adviser, the Trust"
"4664","or such persons as they may designate, solely in connection with the Funds,"
"4665","except as required by applicable law or as otherwise provided hereunder, it"
"4666","being understood and agreed that the Adviser and the Trust may disclose Fund"
"4667","portfolio holdings information in accordance with the Trust's policies and"
"4668","procedures governing the disclosure of Fund portfolio holdings, as amended or"
"4669","supplemented from time to time. Information supplied by the Adviser or the Trust"
"4670","to the Sub-Adviser in connection with performing its obligations under this"
"4671","Agreement shall be treated by the Sub-Adviser as confidential and for use by the"
"4672","Sub-Adviser solely in connection with the Funds and the performance of the"
"4673","Sub-Adviser's obligations hereunder."
"4674","     SECTION 12. RECORDS. The Sub-Adviser shall, with respect to orders the"
"4675","Sub-Adviser places for the purchase and sale of portfolio securities of the"
"4676","Funds, maintain or arrange for the maintenance of the documents and records"
"4677","required pursuant to Rule 31a-1 under the 1940 Act, as well as trade tickets and"
"4678","confirmations of portfolio trades, and such other records as the Adviser"
"4679","reasonably requests to be maintained. All such records shall be maintained in a"
"4680","form reasonably acceptable to the Adviser and the Trust and in compliance with"
"4681","the provisions of Rule 31a-1 or any successor rule. All such records will be the"
"4682","property of the Trust, and will be made available for inspection by the Trust"
"4683","and its authorized representatives (including the Adviser). The Sub-Adviser"
"4684","shall promptly, upon the Trust's written request, surrender to the Trust those"
"4685","records that are the property of the Trust or the Fund; provided, however, that"
"4686","the Sub-Adviser may retain copies of such records."
"4687","     SECTION 13. TERM AND APPROVAL. This Agreement shall become effective with"
"4688","respect to a Fund after it is approved in accordance with the express"
"4689","requirements of the 1940 Act, and executed by the Trust, Adviser and Sub-Adviser"
"4690","and shall thereafter continue from year to year, provided that the continuation"
"4691","of the Agreement is approved in accordance with the requirements of the 1940"
"4692","Act, which currently requires that the continuation be approved at least"
"4693","annually:"
"4694","     (a)  (i) by the Trust's Board of Trustees or (ii) by the vote of a
          majority of the outstanding voting securities of the Fund (as defined"
"4695","          in Section 2(a)(42) of the 1940 Act, and"
"4696","     (b)  by the affirmative vote of a majority of the Trust's Trustees who are"
"4697","          not parties to this Agreement or interested persons (as defined in"
"4698","          the 1940 Act) of a party to this Agreement (other than as Trustees of"
"4699","          the Trust), by votes cast in person at a meeting specifically called"
"4700","          for such purpose."
"4701","     SECTION 14. TERMINATION. This Agreement may be terminated with respect to"
"4702","each Fund at any time, without the payment of any penalty, by vote of the Board"
"4703","or by vote of a majority of the Fund's outstanding voting securities, or by the"
"4704","Adviser or Sub-Adviser upon sixty (60) days' written notice to the other party."
"4705","The notice provided for herein may be waived by the party entitled to receipt"
"4706","thereof. This Agreement shall automatically terminate in the event of its"
"4707","                                      -8-"
"4708","<PAGE>"
"4709","assignment, the term assignment for purposes of this paragraph having the"
"4710","meaning defined in Section 2(a)(4) of the 1940 Act, as it may be interpreted by"
"4711","the Commission or its staff in interpretive releases, or applied by the"
"4712","Commission staff in no-action letters, issued under the 1940 Act."
"4713","     This Agreement may also be terminated immediately by the Adviser, the"
"4714","Sub-Adviser or the Trust in the event that a respective party: (i) breaches a"
"4715","material term of this Agreement; or (ii) commits a material violation of any"
"4716","governing law or regulation; or (iii) engages in conduct that would have a"
"4717","material adverse effect upon the reputation or business prospects of a"
"4718","respective party."
